BLOEMFONTEIN - Firemen from the Mangaung Fire Department were injured when the fire truck they were travelling in sommersaulted on a wet Kenneth Kaunda Road and overturned.The firemen were rushing to an accident scene on the Bultfontein road yesterday afternoon when the fire truck overturned. The accident, in which several firemen were injured, happened at around  13:30, just a few hundred metres from the Northridge Mall in the north of Bloemfontein. No fatalities were reported by authorities. Three people critical after collision... Meanwhile on a separate accident in the city of roses, three people were left injured yesterday morning when two vehicles collided on Holdon Roand in Bloemfontein, leaving two of them critically injured.“ER24 paramedics, along with other services, arrived on the scene to find the SUV in the middle of the road while a light motor vehicle was found on the pavement,” said ER24  in a statement yesterday. Two men, both believed to be 18-years-old, were found by the paramedics lying near their vehicle while a woman, believed to be in her 40s, was found walking around on the scene. Paramedics assessed the injured and found that both men had sustained numerous injuries which left them in a critical condition. On the other hand the woman was found to have sustained only minor injuries. “Paramedics treated the patients and provided the two men with advanced life support interventions. Once treated, the patients were transported to Mediclinic Bloemfontein for further treatment,” reads the statement.According to ER24 the exact cause of the collision is not yet known but local authorities were on the scene for further investigations.